article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 89, Howard Payne 63
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Josh Alexander had 24 points and a team-high 10 rebounds to help lead Stephen F. Austin to an 89-63 win over Howard Payne on Saturday. Alexander shot only 6-of-16 from the field but scored three 3-pointers and hit nine free throws. Kyle Jacobs and Trevor Guy came off the bench to score 13 points apiece for the Lumberjacks (7-5). Scott Weaver added 12 points, including a pair of 3-pointers, and Matt Kingsley had 11 points. The Yellow Jackets (2-8) kept the game close in the first half and led 42-41 at the break. But the Lumberjacks hit 61 percent of their second-half shots compared to 25 percent shooting by Howard Payne. Craig Blackman came off the bench to lead the Yellow Jackets with 13 points. Kendrick Johnson scored 11.
